{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Recognise parenting as a protected character to ensure equality in the workplace",
        "additional_details": "I would like the Government to recognise parenting as a protected character under the Equality Act.\r\n\r\nAs a significant number of the UK work force have young families, they need assurances that they will be treated fairly in their workplace. I would like to see employers more accommodating and more flexible when it comes to adapting flexible working hours or implementing reasonable adjustments. I believe that parenting is as important as other personal character like beliefs, race and gender.\r\n",
        "background": "I have always faced many challenges as a working mother to find a job that allows me to balance my responsibilities as a parent and as a employee.\r\n\r\nOnly recently I realised that being a parent is not a protected character under the UK equality law.\r\n",
